HEADWORD: Pudding wife
<hw>Pudding wife</hw> }</mhw>.
<ety>[Prob. corrupted fr. the Sp. name in Cuba, <ets>pudiano
verde</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large, handsomely colored,
blue and bronze, labroid fish (<spn>Iridio radiatus</spn>, syn.
<spn>Platyglossus radiatus</spn>) of Florida, Bermuda, and the West
Indies. Called also <altname>pudiano</altname>,
<altname>doncella</altname>, and, at Bermuda,
<altname>bluefish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pudding-headed</ent>⟦br⟧
